parcel.description: A gallery dedicated to the 100 unique dog faces and their owners.

features.text:
# SAVAGE DOGS - Artist Statement

The character design exposes two main themes that are constantly present in me, the dog refers to the animal nature in all of us, the good and the bad. The impulses that drive us and how we deal with them. 


The skull-like head points at the unavoidable faith we all face. The dead walking animal, the reminder of time scarcity. 

Both themes are connected to vulnerability and honesty about what we are. We are savages, but we try not to be and that is what I’m passionate about. Our struggle to be more than just animals.

BEK
